cases.demographic.age_at_index.description: The patient's age (in years) on the reference or anchor date used during date obfuscation.

cases.demographic.age_is_obfuscated.description: The age or other properties related to the patient's age have been modified for compliance reasons. The actual age may differ from what was reported in order to comply with the Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act (HIPAA).

cases.demographic.cause_of_death.description: Text term to identify the cause of death for a patient.

cases.demographic.cause_of_death_source.description: The text term used to describe the source used to determine the patient's cause of death.

cases.demographic.country_of_birth.description: The name of the country in which the patient is born.

cases.demographic.country_of_residence_a.description: The text term used to describe the patient's country of residence at the time they were enrolled in the study.

cases.demographic.created_datetime.description: A combination of date and time of day in the form [-]CCYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss[Z|(+|-)hh:mm]

cases.demographic.days_to_birth.description: Number of days between the date used for index and the date from a person's date of birth represented as a calculated negative number of days.

cases.demographic.days_to_death.description: Number of days between the date used for index and the date from a person's date of death represented as a calculated number of days.

cases.demographic.education_level.description: The years of schooling completed in graded public, private, or parochial schools, and in colleges, universities, or professional schools.

cases.demographic.ethnicity.description: An individual's self-described social and cultural grouping, specifically whether an individual describes themselves as Hispanic or Latino. The provided values are based on the categories defined by the U.S. Office of Management and Business and used by the U.S. Census Bureau.

cases.demographic.gender.description: Text designations that identify gender. Gender is described as the assemblage of properties that distinguish people on the basis of their societal roles. [Explanatory Comment 1: Identification of gender is based upon self-report and may come from a form, questionnaire, interview, etc.]

cases.demographic.marital_status.description: A demographic parameter indicating a person's current conjugal status.

cases.demographic.occupation_duration_ye.description: The number of years a patient worked in a specific occupation.

cases.demographic.population_group.description: A group of individuals united by a common factor (e.g., geographic location, ethnicity, disease, age, gender).

cases.demographic.premature_at_birth.description: The yes/no/unknown indicator used to describe whether the patient was premature (less than 37 weeks gestation) at birth.

cases.demographic.race.description: An arbitrary classification of a taxonomic group that is a division of a species. It usually arises as a consequence of geographical isolation within a species and is characterized by shared heredity, physical attributes and behavior, and in the case of humans, by common history, nationality, or geographic distribution. The provided values are based on the categories defined by the U.S. Office of Management and Business and used by the U.S. Census Bureau.

cases.demographic.updated_datetime.description: A combination of date and time of day in the form [-]CCYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss[Z|(+|-)hh:mm]

cases.demographic.vital_status.description: The survival state of the person registered on the protocol.

cases.demographic.weeks_gestation_at_bir.description: Numeric value used to describe the number of weeks starting from the approximate date of the biological mother's last menstrual period and ending with the birth of the patient.

cases.demographic.year_of_birth.description: Numeric value to represent the calendar year in which an individual was born.

cases.demographic.year_of_death.description: Numeric value to represent the year of the death of an individual.

cases.diagnoses.adrenal_hormone.description: Indicates the presence of the adrenal hormone. The adrenal hormone is made from cholesterol and protein produced by the adrenal glands and regulate electrolyte balance, blood pressure, inflammation, blood sugar balance, and immune system control.

cases.diagnoses.age_at_diagnosis.description: Age at the time of diagnosis expressed in number of days since birth.

cases.diagnoses.ajcc_clinical_m.description: Extent of the distant metastasis for the cancer based on evidence obtained from clinical assessment parameters determined prior to treatment.

cases.diagnoses.ajcc_clinical_n.description: Extent of the regional lymph node involvement for the cancer based on evidence obtained from clinical assessment parameters determined prior to treatment.

cases.diagnoses.ajcc_clinical_stage.description: Stage group determined from clinical information on the tumor (T), regional node (N) and metastases (M) and by grouping cases with similar prognosis for cancer.

cases.diagnoses.ajcc_clinical_t.description: Extent of the primary cancer based on evidence obtained from clinical assessment parameters determined prior to treatment.

cases.diagnoses.ajcc_pathologic_m.description: Code to represent the defined absence or presence of distant spread or metastases (M) to locations via vascular channels or lymphatics beyond the regional lymph nodes, using criteria established by the American Joint Committee on Cancer (AJCC).

cases.diagnoses.ajcc_pathologic_n.description: The codes that represent the stage of cancer based on the nodes present (N stage) according to criteria based on multiple editions of the AJCC's Cancer Staging Manual.

cases.diagnoses.ajcc_pathologic_stage.description: The extent of a cancer, especially whether the disease has spread from the original site to other parts of the body based on AJCC staging criteria.

cases.diagnoses.ajcc_pathologic_t.description: Code of pathological T (primary tumor) to define the size or contiguous extension of the primary tumor (T), using staging criteria from the American Joint Committee on Cancer (AJCC).

cases.diagnoses.ajcc_serum_tumor_markers.description: A laboratory test result in which markers for testicular cancer are tested in a blood sample for staging purposes.

cases.diagnoses.ajcc_staging_system_edit.description: The text term used to describe the version or edition of the American Joint Committee on Cancer Staging Handbooks, a publication by the group formed for the purpose of developing a system of staging for cancer that is acceptable to the American medical profession and is compatible with other accepted classifications.

cases.diagnoses.ann_arbor_b_symptoms.description: Text term to signify whether lymphoma B-symptoms are present as noted in the patient's medical record.

cases.diagnoses.ann_arbor_b_symptoms_des.description: Text describing the specific lymphoma B-symptoms present.

cases.diagnoses.ann_arbor_clinical_stage.description: The text term used to describe the clinical classification of lymphoma, as defined by the Ann Arbor Lymphoma Staging System.

cases.diagnoses.ann_arbor_extranodal_inv.description: Indicator that identifies whether a patient with malignant lymphoma has lymphomatous involvement of an extranodal site.

cases.diagnoses.ann_arbor_pathologic_sta.description: The text term used to describe the pathologic classification of lymphoma, as defined by the Ann Arbor Lymphoma Staging System.

cases.diagnoses.annotations.category.description: Top level characterization of the annotation.

cases.diagnoses.annotations.classificati.description: Top level classification of the annotation.

cases.diagnoses.annotations.created_date.description: A combination of date and time of day in the form [-]CCYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss[Z|(+|-)hh:mm]

cases.diagnoses.annotations.creator.description: Name of the person or entity responsible for the creation of the annotation.

cases.diagnoses.annotations.legacy_creat.description: A combination of date and time of day in the form [-]CCYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss[Z|(+|-)hh:mm]

cases.diagnoses.annotations.legacy_updat.description: A combination of date and time of day in the form [-]CCYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss[Z|(+|-)hh:mm]

cases.diagnoses.annotations.notes.description: Open entry for any further description or characterization of the data.

cases.diagnoses.annotations.state.description: The current state of the object.

cases.diagnoses.annotations.submitter_id.description: A project-specific identifier for a node. This property is the calling card/nickname/alias for a unit of submission. It can be used in place of the uuid for identifying or recalling a node.

cases.diagnoses.annotations.updated_date.description: A combination of date and time of day in the form [-]CCYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss[Z|(+|-)hh:mm]

cases.diagnoses.best_overall_response.description: The best improvement achieved throughout the entire course of protocol treatment.

cases.diagnoses.burkitt_lymphoma_clinica.description: Burkitt's lymphoma categorization based on clinical features that differ from other forms of the same disease.

cases.diagnoses.calgb_risk_group.description: A classification strategy for Acute Myeloid Leukemia (AML) developed by the cancer research cooperative group Cancer And Leukemia Group B that assigns a rating based on the cytogenetic and molecular features of a particular disease.

cases.diagnoses.cancer_detection_method.description: The method used to detect disease.

cases.diagnoses.child_pugh_classificatio.description: The text term used to describe the classification used in the prognosis of chronic liver disease, mainly cirrhosis.

cases.diagnoses.clark_level.description: A morphologic finding indicating the cutaneous melanoma depth of invasion into the dermis and subcutaneous tissue.

cases.diagnoses.classification_of_tumor.description: Text that describes the kind of disease present in the tumor specimen as related to a specific timepoint.

cases.diagnoses.cog_liver_stage.description: The text term used to describe the staging classification of liver tumors, as defined by the Children's Oncology Group (COG). This staging system specifically describes the extent of the primary tumor prior to treatment.

cases.diagnoses.cog_neuroblastoma_risk_g.description: Text term that represents the categorization of patients on the basis of prognostic factors per a system developed by Children's Oncology Group (COG). Risk level is used to assign treatment intensity.

cases.diagnoses.cog_renal_stage.description: The text term used to describe the staging classification of renal tumors, as defined by the Children's Oncology Group (COG).

cases.diagnoses.cog_rhabdomyosarcoma_ris.description: Text term used to describe the classification of rhabdomyosarcoma, as defined by the Children's Oncology Group (COG).

cases.diagnoses.contiguous_organ_invaded.description: The organ or contiguous site the disease migrated to from the primary site.

cases.diagnoses.created_datetime.description: A combination of date and time of day in the form [-]CCYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss[Z|(+|-)hh:mm]

cases.diagnoses.days_to_best_overall_res.description: Number of days between the date used for index and the date of the patient was thought to have the best overall response to their disease.

cases.diagnoses.days_to_diagnosis.description: Number of days between the date used for index and the date the patient was diagnosed with the malignant disease.

cases.diagnoses.days_to_last_follow_up.description: Time interval from the date of last follow up to the date of initial pathologic diagnosis, represented as a calculated number of days.

cases.diagnoses.days_to_last_known_disea.description: Number of days between the date used for index and the date the patient's disease status was known.

cases.diagnoses.days_to_recurrence.description: Number of days between the date used for index and the date the patient's disease recurred.

cases.diagnoses.diagnosis_is_primary_dis.description: Indicates whether this specific diagnosis represents the disease that was the primary focus of the study. Additionally, this diagnosis is reflected at the case level, which is captured using the case.disease_type property.

cases.diagnoses.double_expressor_lymphom.description: An immunohistochemical finding indicating the presence of double expression of MYC and BCL2 proteins in the neoplastic cells of a tumor sample.

cases.diagnoses.double_hit_lymphoma.description: A rare B-cell non-Hodgkin lymphoma that is characterized by the abnormal rearrangement of two genes, MYC gene and either BCL2 or BCL6 genes. Patients with this type of lymphoma usually respond poorly to standard treatments and have a poor prognosis.

cases.diagnoses.eln_risk_classification.description: A recommended risk stratification system used to provide prognostic information in AML patients undergoing chemotherapy as well as allogeneic hematopoietic stem cell transplantation.

cases.diagnoses.enneking_msts_grade.description: The text term used to describe the surgical grade of the musculoskeletal sarcoma, using the Enneking staging system approved by the Musculoskeletal Tumor Society (MSTS).

cases.diagnoses.enneking_msts_metastasis.description: Text term and code that represents the metastatic stage of the musculoskeletal sarcoma, using the Enneking staging system approved by the Musculoskeletal Tumor Society (MSTS).

cases.diagnoses.enneking_msts_stage.description: Text term used to describe the stage of the musculoskeletal sarcoma, using the Enneking staging system approved by the Musculoskeletal Tumor Society (MSTS).

cases.diagnoses.enneking_msts_tumor_site.description: Text term and code that represents the tumor site of the musculoskeletal sarcoma, using the Enneking staging system approved by the Musculoskeletal Tumor Society (MSTS).

cases.diagnoses.ensat_clinical_m.description: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of adrenal cancer, following the rules of the ENSAT staging v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

cases.diagnoses.ensat_pathologic_n.description: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of adrenal cancer, following the rules of the ENSAT staging v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the lymph nodes.

cases.diagnoses.ensat_pathologic_stage.description: An adrenal cancer stage defined according to the European Network for the Study of Adrenal Tumors (ENSAT) criteria.

cases.diagnoses.ensat_pathologic_t.description: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of adrenal cancer, following the rules of the ENSAT staging v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

cases.diagnoses.esophageal_columnar_dysp.description: Text term to describe the amount of dysplasia found within the benign esophageal columnar mucosa.

cases.diagnoses.esophageal_columnar_meta.description: The yes/no/unknown indicator used to describe whether esophageal columnar metaplasia was determined to be present.

cases.diagnoses.fab_morphology_code.description: A classification system for acute myeloid leukemias, acute lymphoblastic leukemias, and myelodysplastic syndromes. It is based on the morphologic and cytochemical evaluation of bone marrow and peripheral blood smears.

cases.diagnoses.figo_stage.description: The extent of a cervical or endometrial cancer within the body, especially whether the disease has spread from the original site to other parts of the body, as described by the International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics (FIGO) stages.

cases.diagnoses.figo_staging_edition_yea.description: The text term used to describe the edition year of the FIGO staging system used to stage the patient's gynecologic tumor.

cases.diagnoses.first_symptom_longest_du.description: The length of time the first presenting symptom occurred that related to the diagnosis of the patient with cancer.

cases.diagnoses.first_symptom_prior_to_d.description: Text term used to describe the patient's first symptom experienced prior to diagnosis and thought to be related to the disease.

cases.diagnoses.gastric_esophageal_junct.description: The yes/no/unknown/not reported indicator used to describe whether the tumor is located across the gastroesophageal junction.

cases.diagnoses.gleason_grade_group.description: The text term used to describe the overall grouping of grades defined by the Gleason grading classification, which is used to determine the aggressiveness of prostate cancer. Note that this grade describes the entire prostatectomy specimen and is not specific to the sample used for sequencing.

cases.diagnoses.gleason_grade_tertiary.description: The text term used to describe the tertiary pattern as described by the Gleason Grading System.

cases.diagnoses.gleason_patterns_percent.description: Numeric value that represents the percentage of Patterns 4 and 5, which is used when the Gleason score is greater than 7 to predict prognosis.

cases.diagnoses.gleason_score.description: The score derived from universally embraced prostate cancer grading system developed by Dr. Donald F. Gleason in 1977. The system provides a reproducible description of the glandular architecture of prostate tissue to which a pathologist assigns a score depending primarily on the microscopic patterns of cancerous glands and cell morphology

cases.diagnoses.goblet_cells_columnar_mu.description: The yes/no/unknown indicator used to describe whether goblet cells were determined to be present in the esophageal columnar mucosa.

cases.diagnoses.icd_10_code.description: Alphanumeric value used to describe the disease code from the tenth version of the International Classification of Disease (ICD-10).

cases.diagnoses.igcccg_stage.description: The text term used to describe the International Germ Cell Cancer Collaborative Group (IGCCCG), a grouping used to further classify metastatic testicular tumors.

cases.diagnoses.inpc_grade.description: Text term used to describe the classification of neuroblastic differentiation within neuroblastoma tumors, as defined by the International Neuroblastoma Pathology Classification (INPC).

cases.diagnoses.inpc_histologic_group.description: The text term used to describe the classification of neuroblastomas distinguishing between favorable and unfavorable histologic groups. The histologic score, defined by the International Neuroblastoma Pathology Classification (INPC), is based on age, mitosis-karyorrhexis index (MKI), stromal content and degree of tumor cell differentiation.

cases.diagnoses.inrg_stage.description: The text term used to describe the staging classification of neuroblastic tumors, as defined by the International Neuroblastoma Risk Group (INRG).

cases.diagnoses.inss_stage.description: Text term used to describe the staging classification of neuroblastic tumors, as defined by the International Neuroblastoma Staging System (INSS).

cases.diagnoses.international_prognostic.description: The text term used to describe the International Prognostic Index, which classifies the prognosis of patients with aggressive non-Hodgkin's lymphoma.

cases.diagnoses.irs_group.description: Text term used to describe the classification of rhabdomyosarcoma tumors, as defined by the Intergroup Rhabdomyosarcoma Study (IRS).

cases.diagnoses.irs_stage.description: The text term used to describe the classification of rhabdomyosarcoma tumors, as defined by the Intergroup Rhabdomyosarcoma Study (IRS).

cases.diagnoses.ishak_fibrosis_score.description: The text term used to describe the classification of the histopathologic degree of liver damage.

cases.diagnoses.iss_stage.description: The multiple myeloma disease stage at diagnosis.

cases.diagnoses.last_known_disease_statu.description: Text term that describes the last known state or condition of an individual's neoplasm.

cases.diagnoses.laterality.description: For tumors in paired organs, designates the side on which the cancer originates.

cases.diagnoses.margin_distance.description: Numeric value that represents the distance between the tumor and the surgical margin

cases.diagnoses.margins_involved_site.description: The text term used to describe the anatomic sites that were involved in the survival margins.

cases.diagnoses.masaoka_stage.description: The text term used to describe the Masaoka staging system, a classification that defines prognostic indicators for thymic malignancies and predicts tumor recurrence.

cases.diagnoses.max_tumor_bulk_site.description: The site of the tumor where the dimension or diameter is larger than any other part of the tumor.

cases.diagnoses.medulloblastoma_molecula.description: The text term used to describe the classification of medulloblastoma tumors based on molecular features.

cases.diagnoses.melanoma_known_primary.description: A melanoma which has metastasized from a known primary anatomic site.

cases.diagnoses.metastasis_at_diagnosis.description: The text term used to describe the extent of metastatic disease present at diagnosis.

cases.diagnoses.metastasis_at_diagnosis_.description: Text term to identify an anatomic site in which metastatic disease involvement is found.

cases.diagnoses.method_of_diagnosis.description: Text term used to describe the method used to confirm the patients malignant diagnosis.

cases.diagnoses.micropapillary_features.description: The yes/no/unknown indicator used to describe whether micropapillary features were determined to be present.

cases.diagnoses.mitosis_karyorrhexis_ind.description: Text term that represents the component of the International Neuroblastoma Pathology Classification (INPC) for mitosis-karyorrhexis index (MKI).

cases.diagnoses.mitotic_count.description: The number of mitoses identified under the microscope in tumors. The method of counting varies, according to the specific tumor examined. Usually, the mitotic count is determined based on the number of mitoses per high power field (40X) or 10 high power fields.

cases.diagnoses.morphology.description: The third edition of the International Classification of Diseases for Oncology, published in 2000 used principally in tumor and cancer registries for coding the site (topography) and the histology (morphology) of neoplasms. The study of the structure of the cells and their arrangement to constitute tissues and, finally, the association among these to form organs. In pathology, the microscopic process of identifying normal and abnormal morphologic characteristics in tissues, by employing various cytochemical and immunocytochemical stains. A system of numbered categories for representation of data.

cases.diagnoses.ovarian_specimen_status.description: The text term used to describe the physical condition of the involved ovary.

cases.diagnoses.ovarian_surface_involvem.description: The text term that describes whether the surface tissue (outer boundary) of the ovary shows evidence of involvement or presence of cancer.

cases.diagnoses.papillary_renal_cell_typ.description: The text term used to describe the type of papillary renal cell carcinoma characterized by the presence of papillae covered by small cells with scant amount of cytoplasm.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.additi.description: A section header that includes additional pathologic findings.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.anapla.description: Yes/no/unknown/not reported indicator used to describe whether anaplasia was present at the time of diagnosis.

The text term used to describe the morphologic findings indicating the presence of a malignant cellular infiltrate characterized by the presence of large pleomorphic cells, necrosis, and high mitotic activity in a tissue sample.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.bone_m.description: The text term used to indicate whether there are malignant cells in the bone marrow.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.breslo.description: The number that describes the distance, in millimeters, between the upper layer of the epidermis and the deepest point of tumor penetration.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.circum.description: Numeric value used to describe the non-peritonealised bare area of rectum, comprising anterior and posterior segments, when submitted as a surgical specimen resulting from excision of cancer of the rectum.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.column.description: Indicator noting whether columnar mucosa was present within the tissue.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.consis.description: Indicates whether a recent review of tissue is consistent with a prior pathology review.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.create.description: A combination of date and time of day in the form [-]CCYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss[Z|(+|-)hh:mm]

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.days_t.description: Number of days between the date used for index and the date a pathologic review of a specific sample or slide was performed.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.dyspla.description: The degree to which dysplasia was involved.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.epithe.description: A quantitative measurement of the percent of epithelioid melanocytes compared to the number of total cells present in a sample.
A quantitative measurement of the percent of epithelioid melanocytes compared to the number of total cells present in a sample.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.extrac.description: The extension of malignant tissue situated outside of a specific capsule.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.extran.description: Extension of a malignant neoplasm beyond the lymph node capsule.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.extrao.description: The size of the nodule that is outside the eye.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.extras.description: Spread of uveal melanoma beyond the sclera.
Spread of uveal melanoma beyond the sclera.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.extrat.description: Text term to describe the degree to which the primary tumor has extra thyroid extension.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.greate.description: Numeric value that represents the measurement of the widest portion of the tumor in centimeters.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.gross_.description: Numeric value used to describe the gross pathologic tumor weight, measured in grams.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.histol.description: Text term to describe the disease progression as determined by microscopic review of cells and their surrounding extracellular environment in tissues.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.intrat.description: Text term to indicate whether the intratubular germ cell neoplasm is present or absent.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.larges.description: The text term used to describe the diameter of the largest focus originating outside of the pelvic peritoneal region.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.lymph_.description: The method employed to remove a lymph nodes(s)
The named location(s) within the body where a lymph node(s) were removed.
The text term used to describe the anatomic site of lymph node involvement.
Indicator noting whether lymph nodes were involved.
The number of lymph nodes involved with disease as determined by pathologic examination.
The number of lymph nodes removed during a biopsy or surgical procedure.
The number of lymph nodes tested to determine whether lymph nodes were involved with disease as determined by a pathologic examination.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.lympha.description: A yes/no indicator to ask if small or thin-walled vessel invasion is present, indicating lymphatic involvement

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.margin.description: The determination of the presence of actual or potential neoplastic tissue which has been left outside the boundary of a resected specimen within the patient.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.measur.description: The method used to measure tumor size.
The type of unit of measure being used to express a length or distance.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.metapl.description: Indicator noting whether metaplasia was present.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.microm.description: Indication of metastasis in the form of small clusters of malignant cells identifiable only under the microscope.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.morpho.description: A specific morphologic or pathologic architectural pattern was discovered within the sample studied.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.necros.description: A quantitative measurement of the percent of cells undergoing necrosis compared to the number of total cells present in a sample.
Indicator describing whether the presence of necrosis was confirmed.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.non_no.description: The text term used to describe whether the patient had non-nodal regional disease.
The yes/no/unknown indicator used to describe the presence of tumor deposits in the pericolic or perirectal fat or in adjacent mesentery away from the leading edge of the tumor.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.number.description: Numeric value that represents the count of proliferating cells determined during pathologic review of the sample slide(s).

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.percen.description: The percentage of tumor cells spread locally in a malignant neoplasm through infiltration or destruction of adjacent tissue.
Numeric value to represent the percentage of tumor nuclei in a malignant neoplasm sample or specimen.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.perine.description: a yes/no indicator to ask if perineural invasion or infiltration of tumor or cancer is present.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.peripa.description: Enumerated numeric value or range of values used to describe the number of peripancreatic lymph nodes determined to be positive.
The total number of peripancreatic lymph nodes tested for the presence of pancreatic cancer cells.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.prcc_t.description: The type of papillary renal cell carcinoma. It is classified as type 1 or 2, based on the cytoplasmic volume and the thickness of the lining neoplastic cells.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.prosta.description: The text term used to describe the number of positive prostatic chips, which are generated from transurethral resection of the prostate (TURP) procedures and are generally used for relieving urinary obstruction due to nodular hyperplasia of the prostate (benign prostatic hyperplasia).

The text term used to describe the total number of prostatic chips, which are generated from transurethral resection of the prostate (TURP) procedures and are generally used for relieving urinary obstruction due to nodular hyperplasia of the prostate (benign prostatic hyperplasia).
Numeric value that represents the percentage of prostatic involvement found in a specific tissue sample.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.residu.description: Tumor cells that remain in the body following cancer treatment.
A measurement of the tumor cells that remain in the body following cancer treatment.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.rhabdo.description: Numeric value that represents the percentage of rhabdoid features found in a specific tissue sample.
Indicator describing whether rhabdoid features were present.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.sarcom.description: Numeric value that represents the percentage of sarcomatoid features found in a specific tissue sample.
Indicator describing whether sarcomatoid features were present.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.size_e.description: The size of the nodule that is outside the eye.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.spindl.description: A quantitative measurement of the percent of spindle-shaped melanocytes compared to the number of total cells present in a sample.
A quantitative measurement of the percent of spindle-shaped melanocytes compared to the number of total cells present in a sample.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.state.description: The current state of the object.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.submit.description: A project-specific identifier for a node. This property is the calling card/nickname/alias for a unit of submission. It can be used in place of the uuid for identifying or recalling a node.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.timepo.description: Category describing a specific point in the time continuum, including those established relative to an event.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.transg.description: The text term used to describe an extension of the tumor beyond the opening into the ventricles and vocal cords.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.tumor_.description: Numeric value in millimeters for the lowest layer of a tumor.
Refers to the number of cancer cells, the size of a tumor, or the amount of cancer in the body.
Text term for the degree to which a tumor has penetrated into organ or tissue.
The numerical measurement of tumor depth.
Lymphocytes that show specificity for autologous tumor cells and can infiltrate a tumor.
Non-neoplastic macrophages that infiltrate a tumor.
Numeric value used to describe the maximum diameter or dimension of the primary tumor, measured in centimeters.
The numerical measurement of tumor length.
The level(s) of the prostate from which the tumor originated.
Text term to represent the description of the shape of a tumor determined by clinical or pathological techniques.
A measurement of the thickness of a sectioned slice (of tissue or mineral or other substance) in millimeters (mm).
The numerical measurement of tumor width.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.update.description: A combination of date and time of day in the form [-]CCYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss[Z|(+|-)hh:mm]

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.vascul.description: The yes/no indicator to ask if large vessel or venous invasion was detected by surgery or presence in a tumor specimen.
Text term that represents the type of vascular tumor invasion.

cases.diagnoses.pathology_details.zone_o.description: The location or position of the tumor by zone of the prostate.

cases.diagnoses.pediatric_kidney_staging.description: A modified version of the Children's Oncology Group (COG) National Wilms Tumor Study Group (NWTS) staging system.

cases.diagnoses.peritoneal_fluid_cytolog.description: The text term used to describe the malignant status of the peritoneal fluid determined by cytologic testing.

cases.diagnoses.pregnant_at_diagnosis.description: The text term used to indicate whether the patient was pregnant at the time they were diagnosed.

cases.diagnoses.primary_diagnosis.description: Text term used to describe the patient's histologic diagnosis, as described by the World Health Organization's (WHO) International Classification of Diseases for Oncology (ICD-O).

cases.diagnoses.primary_disease.description: Indicates whether the specific diagnosis represents the disease that was the primary focus of the study.

cases.diagnoses.primary_gleason_grade.description: The text term used to describe the primary Gleason score, which describes the pattern of cells making up the largest area of the tumor. The primary and secondary Gleason pattern grades are combined to determine the patient's Gleason grade group, which is used to determine the aggresiveness of prostate cancer. Note that this grade describes the entire prostatectomy specimen and is not specific to the sample used for sequencing.

cases.diagnoses.prior_malignancy.description: The yes/no/unknown indicator used to describe the patient's history of prior cancer diagnosis.

cases.diagnoses.prior_treatment.description: A yes/no/unknown/not applicable indicator related to the administration of therapeutic agents received before the body specimen was collected.

cases.diagnoses.progression_or_recurrenc.description: Indicates whether a patient has a progression or recurrence after initial treatment. This can include local, regional, or metastatic disease.

cases.diagnoses.residual_disease.description: Tumor cells that remain in the body following cancer treatment.

cases.diagnoses.satellite_nodule_present.description: Indicator noting whether a nodule or tumor is located within a small distance (e.g. 2cm) of the primary tumor.

cases.diagnoses.secondary_gleason_grade.description: The text term used to describe the secondary Gleason score, which describes the pattern of cells making up the second largest area of the tumor. cases.diagnoses.site_of_resection_or_bio.description: The text term used to describe the anatomic site of origin, of the patient's malignant disease, as described by the World Health Organization's (WHO) International Classification of Diseases for Oncology (ICD-O).

cases.diagnoses.sites_of_involvement.description: The anatomic sites of disease involvement in addition to the primary anatomic site.

cases.diagnoses.sites_of_involvement_cou.description: The number of anatomic sites of disease.

cases.diagnoses.supratentorial_localizat.description: Text term to specify the location of the supratentorial tumor.

cases.diagnoses.synchronous_malignancy.description: A yes/no/unknown indicator used to describe whether the patient had an additional malignant diagnosis at the same time the tumor used for sequencing was diagnosed. If both tumors were sequenced, both tumors would have synchronous malignancies.

cases.diagnoses.tissue_or_organ_of_origi.description: The text term used to describe the anatomic site of origin, of the patient's malignant disease, as described by the World Health Organization's (WHO) International Classification of Diseases for Oncology (ICD-O).

cases.diagnoses.treatments.chemo_concurr.description: The text term used to describe whether the patient was receiving chemotherapy concurrent to radiation.

cases.diagnoses.treatments.clinical_tria.description: Indicator used to describe whether the treatment was part of a clinical trial.

cases.diagnoses.treatments.course_number.description: The number assigned to a course of therapeutic agent administration, indicating where a particular course of treatment falls within a sequence of treatments.

cases.diagnoses.treatments.drug_category.description: A broad categorization of the type of drug administered.

cases.diagnoses.treatments.embolic_agent.description: A substance used to block an artery, thereby eliminating the blood flow to a specific part of an organ. An embolic agent may cause permanent or temporary blockage depending on the nature of the material used.

cases.diagnoses.treatments.initial_disea.description: The text term used to describe the status of the patient's malignancy when the treatment began.

cases.diagnoses.treatments.margin_distan.description: Numeric value that represents the distance between the tumor and the surgical margin

cases.diagnoses.treatments.margin_status.description: The determination of the presence of actual or potential neoplastic tissue which has been left outside the boundary of a resected specimen within the patient.

cases.diagnoses.treatments.margins_invol.description: The text term used to describe the anatomic sites that were involved in the survival margins.

cases.diagnoses.treatments.number_of_cyc.description: The numeric value used to describe the number of cycles of a specific treatment or regimen the patient received.

cases.diagnoses.treatments.number_of_fra.description: The total number of divided radiation doses received.

cases.diagnoses.treatments.prescribed_do.description: A quantity of an agent prescribed to the study participant.

cases.diagnoses.treatments.pretreatment.description: Any relevant actions that were performed or occurred prior to a specific treatment.

cases.diagnoses.treatments.protocol_iden.description: A sequence of letters, numbers, or other characters that uniquely identifies a study protocol.

cases.diagnoses.treatments.radiosensitiz.description: Indication if an agent that makes tumor cells more sensitive to radiation therapy was used in treatment.

cases.diagnoses.treatments.reason_treatm.description: The text term used to describe the reason a specific treatment or regimen ended.
The reason the treatment was not administered.

cases.diagnoses.treatments.regimen_or_li.description: The text term used to describe the regimen or line of therapy.

cases.diagnoses.treatments.residual_dise.description: Tumor cells that remain in the body following cancer treatment.

cases.diagnoses.treatments.route_of_admi.description: The pathway by which a substance is administered in order to reach the site of action in the body.

cases.diagnoses.treatments.therapeutic_a.description: Text identification of the individual agent(s) used as part of a treatment regimen.

cases.diagnoses.treatments.therapeutic_l.description: Indicates a target level of treatment was reached, according to the patient's treatment plan.

cases.diagnoses.treatments.therapeutic_t.description: Describes a specific target for an administered treatment.

cases.diagnoses.treatments.timepoint_cat.description: Category describing a specific point in the time continuum, including those established relative to an event.

cases.diagnoses.treatments.treatment_ana.description: The anatomic site or field targeted by a treatment regimen or single agent therapy.
The anatomic site or field targeted by a treatment regimen or single agent therapy.

cases.diagnoses.treatments.treatment_arm.description: Text term used to describe the treatment arm assigned to a patient at the time eligibility is determined.

cases.diagnoses.treatments.treatment_dos.description: The numeric value used to describe the total dose of an agent the patient received.
A maximum quantity of an agent administered to the study participant.
The text term used to describe the dose units of an agent the patient received.

cases.diagnoses.treatments.treatment_dur.description: The number of days during which the treatment was given.

cases.diagnoses.treatments.treatment_eff.description: The text term used to describe the pathologic effect a treatment(s) had on the tumor.
The text term used to indicate whether the treatment had an effect on the patient.

cases.diagnoses.treatments.treatment_fre.description: The text term used to describe the frequency the patient received an agent or regimen.

cases.diagnoses.treatments.treatment_int.description: Text term to identify the reason for the administration of a treatment regimen. [Manually-curated]

cases.diagnoses.treatments.treatment_or_.description: A yes/no/unknown/not applicable indicator related to the administration of therapeutic agents received.

cases.diagnoses.treatments.updated_datet.description: A combination of date and time of day in the form [-]CCYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss[Z|(+|-)hh:mm]

cases.diagnoses.tumor_burden.description: Refers to the number of cancer cells, the size of a tumor, or the amount of cancer in the body.

cases.diagnoses.tumor_confined_to_organ_.description: The yes/no/unknown indicator used to describe whether the tumor is confined to the organ where it originated and did not spread to a proximal or distant location within the body.

cases.diagnoses.tumor_depth.description: Numeric value that represents the depth of tumor invasion, measured in millimeters (mm).

cases.diagnoses.tumor_focality.description: The text term used to describe whether the patient's disease originated in a single location or multiple locations.

cases.diagnoses.tumor_grade.description: Numeric value to express the degree of abnormality of cancer cells, a measure of differentiation and aggressiveness.

cases.diagnoses.tumor_grade_category.description: Describes the number of levels or 'tiers' in the system used to determine the degree of tumor differentiation.

cases.diagnoses.tumor_of_origin.description: The submitter_id string of the primary diagnosis node.

cases.diagnoses.tumor_regression_grade.description: A numeric value used to measure therapeutic response of the primary tumor and predict patient outcomes based on a three-point tumor regression grading system.

cases.diagnoses.uicc_clinical_m.description: The UICC TNM Classification is an anatomically based system that records the primary and regional nodal extent of the tumor and the absence or presence of metastases. The clinical M category describes the presence or otherwise of distant metastatic spread as determined during a clinical exam.

cases.diagnoses.uicc_clinical_n.description: The UICC TNM Classification is an anatomically based system that records the primary and regional nodal extent of the tumor and the absence or presence of metastases. The clinical N category describes the regional lymph node involvement as determined during a clinical exam.

cases.diagnoses.uicc_clinical_stage.description: The UICC TNM Classification is an anatomically based system that records the primary and regional nodal extent of the tumor and the absence or presence of metastases. The clinical stage is based on the T, N, and M categories which are determined during a clinical exam.

cases.diagnoses.uicc_clinical_t.description: The UICC TNM Classification is an anatomically based system that records the primary and regional nodal extent of the tumor and the absence or presence of metastases. The clinical T category describes the primary tumor site and size as determined during a clinical exam.

cases.diagnoses.uicc_pathologic_m.description: The UICC TNM Classification is an anatomically based system that records the primary and regional nodal extent of the tumor and the absence or presence of metastases. The pathological M category describes the presence or otherwise of distant metastatic spread as determined during a pathology review.

cases.diagnoses.uicc_pathologic_n.description: The UICC TNM Classification is an anatomically based system that records the primary and regional nodal extent of the tumor and the absence or presence of metastases. The pathological N category describes the regional lymph node involvement as determined during a pathology review.

cases.diagnoses.uicc_pathologic_stage.description: The UICC TNM Classification is an anatomically based system that records the primary and regional nodal extent of the tumor and the absence or presence of metastases. The pathological stage is based on the T, N, and M categories which are determined during a pathological review.

cases.diagnoses.uicc_pathologic_t.description: The UICC TNM Classification is an anatomically based system that records the primary and regional nodal extent of the tumor and the absence or presence of metastases. The pathological T category describes the primary tumor site and size as determined during a pathology review.

cases.diagnoses.uicc_staging_system_edit.description: The UICC TNM Classification is an anatomically based system that records the primary and regional nodal extent of the tumor and the absence or presence of metastases. The staging edition describes the specific UICC edition used when a patient's stage was determined.

cases.diagnoses.ulceration_indicator.description: The formation or development of an ulcer.

cases.diagnoses.updated_datetime.description: A combination of date and time of day in the form [-]CCYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss[Z|(+|-)hh:mm]

cases.diagnoses.weiss_assessment_finding.description: Histopathologic criteria to evaluate adrenocortical tumors.

cases.diagnoses.weiss_assessment_score.description: The text term used to describe the overall Weiss assessment score, a commonly used assessment describing the malignancy of adrenocortical tumors. The Weiss score is determined based on nine histological criteria including the following: high nuclear grade, mitotic rate greater than five per 50 high power fields (HPF), atypical mitotic figures, eosinophilic tumor cell cytoplasm (greater than 75% tumor cells), diffuse architecture (greater than 33% of tumor), necrosis, venous invasion, sinusoidal invasion, and capsular invasion.

cases.diagnoses.who_cns_grade.description: The WHO (World Health Organization) grading classification of CNS tumors, which is based on histological characteristics such as cellularity, mitotic activity, pleomorphism, necrosis, and endothelial proliferation (neoangiogenesis).

cases.diagnoses.who_nte_grade.description: The WHO (World Health Organization) grading classification of Neuroendocrine Tumors.

cases.diagnoses.wilms_tumor_histologic_s.description: The text term used to describe the classification of Wilms tumors distinguishing between favorable and unfavorable histologic groups.

cases.diagnoses.year_of_diagnosis.description: Numeric value to represent the year of an individual's initial pathologic diagnosis of cancer.

cases.exposures.age_at_last_exposure.description: The study participant's age at the time they were last exposed.

cases.exposures.age_at_onset.description: Numeric value used to represent the age of the patient when exposure to a specific environmental factor began.

cases.exposures.alcohol_days_per_week.description: Numeric value used to describe the average number of days each week that a person consumes an alcoholic beverage.

cases.exposures.alcohol_drinks_per_day.description: Numeric value used to describe the average number of alcoholic beverages a person consumes per day.

cases.exposures.alcohol_frequency.description: Describes how often the subject drinks alcohol.

cases.exposures.alcohol_history.description: A response to a question that asks whether the participant has consumed at least 12 drinks of any kind of alcoholic beverage in their lifetime.

cases.exposures.alcohol_intensity.description: Category to describe the patient's current level of alcohol use as self-reported by the patient.

cases.exposures.asbestos_exposure.description: The yes/no/unknown indicator used to describe whether the patient was exposed to asbestos.

cases.exposures.asbestos_exposure_type.description: The type of asbestos exposure the study participant experienced.

cases.exposures.chemical_exposure_type.description: The specific type of contact with a chemical substance through touch, inhalation, or ingestion.

cases.exposures.cigarettes_per_day.description: The average number of cigarettes smoked per day.

cases.exposures.coal_dust_exposure.description: The yes/no/unknown indicator used to describe whether a patient was exposed to fine powder derived by the crushing of coal.

cases.exposures.created_datetime.description: A combination of date and time of day in the form [-]CCYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss[Z|(+|-)hh:mm]

cases.exposures.environmental_tobacco_sm.description: The yes/no/unknown indicator used to describe whether a patient was exposed to smoke that is emitted from burning tobacco, including cigarettes, pipes, and cigars. This includes tobacco smoke exhaled by smokers.

cases.exposures.exposure_duration.description: Text term used to describe the length of time the patient was exposed to an environmental factor.

cases.exposures.exposure_duration_hrs_pe.description: The duration (in hours per day) that a person was exposed.

cases.exposures.exposure_duration_years.description: The period of time from start to finish of exposure, in years.

cases.exposures.exposure_source.description: The source or location where the patient was exposed.

cases.exposures.exposure_type.description: The text term used to describe the type of environmental exposure.

cases.exposures.occupation_duration_year.description: The number of years a patient worked in a specific occupation.

cases.exposures.occupation_type.description: A categorization of the principal activity that a person does to earn money, as defined by the International Classification of Occupation (ISCO).

cases.exposures.pack_years_smoked.description: Numeric computed value to represent lifetime tobacco exposure defined as number of cigarettes smoked per day x number of years smoked divided by 20.

cases.exposures.parent_with_radiation_ex.description: Indicates whether the patient's parent(s) were exposed to radiation

cases.exposures.radon_exposure.description: The yes/no/unknown indicator used to describe whether the patient was exposed to radon.

cases.exposures.respirable_crystalline_s.description: The yes/no/unknown indicator used to describe whether a patient was exposed to respirable crystalline silica, a widespread, naturally occurring, crystalline metal oxide that consists of different forms including quartz, cristobalite, tridymite, tripoli, ganister, chert, and novaculite.

cases.exposures.secondhand_smoke_as_chil.description: The text term used to indicate whether the patient was exposed to secondhand smoke as a child.

cases.exposures.smoking_frequency.description: The text term used to generally describe how often the patient smokes.

cases.exposures.submitter_id.description: A project-specific identifier for a node. This property is the calling card/nickname/alias for a unit of submission. It can be used in place of the uuid for identifying or recalling a node.

cases.exposures.time_between_waking_and_.description: The text term used to describe the approximate amount of time elapsed between the time the patient wakes up in the morning to the time they smoke their first cigarette.

cases.exposures.tobacco_smoking_onset_ye.description: The year in which the participant began smoking.

cases.exposures.tobacco_smoking_quit_yea.description: The year in which the participant quit smoking.

cases.exposures.tobacco_smoking_status.description: Category describing current smoking status and smoking history as self-reported by a patient.

cases.exposures.type_of_smoke_exposure.description: The text term used to describe the patient's specific type of smoke exposure.

cases.exposures.type_of_tobacco_used.description: The text term used to describe the specific type of tobacco used by the patient.

cases.exposures.updated_datetime.description: A combination of date and time of day in the form [-]CCYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss[Z|(+|-)hh:mm]

cases.exposures.use_per_day.description: The average number of times the patient used per day.

cases.exposures.years_smoked.description: Numeric value (or unknown) to represent the number of years a person has been smoking.

cases.family_histories.created_datetime.description: A combination of date and time of day in the form [-]CCYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss[Z|(+|-)hh:mm]

cases.family_histories.relationship_age_.description: The age (in years) when the patient's relative was first diagnosed.

cases.family_histories.relationship_gend.description: The text term used to describe the gender of the patient's relative with a history of cancer.

cases.family_histories.relationship_type.description: The subgroup that describes the state of connectedness between members of the unit of society organized around kinship ties.

cases.family_histories.relative_deceased.description: The historical fact that a legal or consanguineous family member has died.

cases.family_histories.relative_smoker.description: Indication that a legal or consanguineous family member was a smoker.

cases.family_histories.relative_with_can.description: The yes/no/unknown indicator used to describe whether any of the patient's relatives have a history of cancer.

cases.family_histories.relatives_with_ca.description: The number of relatives the patient has with a known history of cancer.

cases.family_histories.submitter_id.description: A project-specific identifier for a node. This property is the calling card/nickname/alias for a unit of submission. It can be used in place of the uuid for identifying or recalling a node.

cases.family_histories.updated_datetime.description: A combination of date and time of day in the form [-]CCYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss[Z|(+|-)hh:mm]

cases.follow_ups.adverse_event.description: Text that represents the Common Terminology Criteria for Adverse Events low level term name for an adverse event.

cases.follow_ups.adverse_event_grade.description: Numeric representation of the intensity/severity of an unfavorable and unintended sign (including an abnormal laboratory finding), symptom, syndrome, or disease, temporally associated with the use of a medical product or procedure, regardless of whether or not it is considered related to the product or procedure (attribution of unrelated, unlikely, possible, probable, or definite).

cases.follow_ups.aids_risk_factors.description: The text term used to describe a risk factor of the acquired immunodeficiency syndrome (AIDS) that the patient either had at the time of the study or experienced in the past.

cases.follow_ups.barretts_esophagus_gobl.description: The yes/no/unknown indicator used to describe whether goblet cells were determined to be present in a patient diagnosed with Barrett's esophagus.

cases.follow_ups.bmi.description: A calculated numerical quantity that represents an individual's weight to height ratio.

cases.follow_ups.body_surface_area.description: Numeric value used to represent the two-dimensional extent of the body surface relating height to weight.

cases.follow_ups.cause_of_response.description: The text term used to describe the suspected cause or reason for the patient disease response.

cases.follow_ups.cd4_count.description: The text term used to describe the outcome of the procedure to determine the amount of the CD4 expressing cells in a sample.

cases.follow_ups.cdc_hiv_risk_factors.description: The text term used to describe a risk factor for human immunodeficiency virus, as described by the Centers for Disease Control.

cases.follow_ups.comorbidities.description: The text term used to describe a patient with one or more diseases or conditions, which coexist with the patient's malignant disease at the same time.

cases.follow_ups.comorbidity.description: The text term used to describe a comorbidity disease, which coexists with the patient's malignant disease.

cases.follow_ups.comorbidity_method_of_d.description: The text term used to describe the method used to diagnose the patient's comorbid disease.

cases.follow_ups.days_to_progression.description: Number of days between the date used for index and the date the patient's disease progressed.

cases.follow_ups.days_to_progression_fre.description: Number of days between the date used for index and the date the patient's disease was formally confirmed as progression-free.

cases.follow_ups.days_to_recurrence.description: Number of days between the date used for index and the date the patient's disease recurred.

cases.follow_ups.days_to_risk_factor.description: The number of days from the index date to the date the patient was diagnosed with a specific risk factor.

cases.follow_ups.diabetes_treatment_type.description: Text term used to describe the types of treatment used to manage diabetes.

cases.follow_ups.discontiguous_lesion_co.description: The number of the discontiguous lesions in a new tumor event.

cases.follow_ups.disease_response.description: Code assigned to describe the patient's response or outcome to the disease.

cases.follow_ups.dlco_ref_predictive_per.description: The value, as a percentage of predicted lung volume, measuring the amount of carbon monoxide detected in a patient's lungs.

cases.follow_ups.ecog_performance_status.description: The ECOG functional performance status of the patient/participant.

cases.follow_ups.evidence_of_progression.description: The text term used to describe the type of evidence used to determine whether the patient's disease progressed.

cases.follow_ups.evidence_of_recurrence_.description: The text term used to describe the type of evidence used to determine whether the patient's disease recurred.

cases.follow_ups.eye_color.description: The color of the iris of the eye

cases.follow_ups.fev1_fvc_post_bronch_pe.description: Percentage value to represent result of Forced Expiratory Volume in 1 second (FEV1) divided by the Forced Vital Capacity (FVC) post-bronchodilator.

cases.follow_ups.fev1_fvc_pre_bronch_per.description: Percentage value to represent result of Forced Expiratory Volume in 1 second (FEV1) divided by the Forced Vital Capacity (FVC) pre-bronchodilator.

cases.follow_ups.fev1_ref_post_bronch_pe.description: The percentage comparison to a normal value reference range of the volume of air that a patient can forcibly exhale from the lungs in one second post-bronchodilator.

cases.follow_ups.fev1_ref_pre_bronch_per.description: The percentage comparison to a normal value reference range of the volume of air that a patient can forcibly exhale from the lungs in one second pre-bronchodilator.

cases.follow_ups.first_event.description: Describes the patient's first event after initial treatment.

cases.follow_ups.haart_treatment_indicat.description: The text term used to indicate whether the patient received Highly Active Antiretroviral Therapy (HAART).

cases.follow_ups.height.description: The height of the patient in centimeters.

cases.follow_ups.hepatitis_sustained_vir.description: An indication as to whether sustained virological response was obtained in responses to viral hepatitis treatment.

cases.follow_ups.histologic_progression.description: The evolution of a low-grade neoplastic pathologic process to a high grade malignancy.

cases.follow_ups.history_of_tumor.description: Indicates whether patient has a history of tumors.

cases.follow_ups.history_of_tumor_type.description: Describes the type of the patient's prior diagnosed tumor.

cases.follow_ups.hiv_viral_load.description: Numeric value that represents the concentration of an analyte or aliquot extracted from the sample or sample portion, measured in milligrams per milliliter.

cases.follow_ups.hormonal_contraceptive_.description: The specific type of hormonal contraceptives used by the subject.
The text term used to indicate whether the patient used hormonal contraceptives.

cases.follow_ups.hormone_replacement_the.description: The specific type of hormone replacement therapy received by the patient.

cases.follow_ups.hpv_positive_type.description: Text classification to represent the strain or type of human papillomavirus identified in an individual.

cases.follow_ups.hysterectomy_margins_in.description: The text term used to indicate whether the patient's disease was determined to be involved based on the surgical margins of the hysterectomy.

cases.follow_ups.hysterectomy_type.description: The text term used to describe the type of hysterectomy the patient had.

cases.follow_ups.imaging_anatomic_site.description: The named location(s) within the body where an image was taken.

cases.follow_ups.imaging_findings.description: Recorded findings noted during the review of a specific medical image.

cases.follow_ups.imaging_result.description: The text term used to describe the result of the imaging or scan performed on the patient.

cases.follow_ups.imaging_suv.description: The standardized update value (SUV) is the effectively dimensionless measure of regional tracer uptake calculated as the activity concentration within a 2D region of interest (ROI) or 3D volume of interest (VOI) measured on a PET image (nCi1mL) / [injected dose (nCi) / body weight (g)].

cases.follow_ups.imaging_suv_max.description: The standardized update value (SUV) is the effectively dimensionless measure of regional tracer uptake calculated as the activity concentration within a 2D region of interest (ROI) or 3D volume of interest (VOI) measured on a PET image (nCi1mL) / [injected dose (nCi) / body weight (g)]. Specifically, the maximum SUV recorded for a patient.

cases.follow_ups.imaging_type.description: The text term used to describe the type of imaging or scan performed on the patient.

cases.follow_ups.immunosuppressive_treat.description: The text term used to describe the type of immunosuppressive treatment the patient received.

cases.follow_ups.karnofsky_performance_s.description: Text term used to describe the classification used of the functional capabilities of a person.

cases.follow_ups.menopause_status.description: Text term used to describe the patient's menopause status.

cases.follow_ups.molecular_tests.aa_chan.description: Alphanumeric value used to describe the amino acid change for a specific genetic variant. Example: R116Q.

cases.follow_ups.molecular_tests.aneuplo.description: A chromosomal abnormality in which there is an addition or loss of chromosomes within a set (e.g., 23 + 22 or 23 + 24).

cases.follow_ups.molecular_tests.antigen.description: The text term used to describe an antigen included in molecular testing.

cases.follow_ups.molecular_tests.biospec.description: The text term used to describe the biological material used for testing, diagnostic, treatment or research purposes.

cases.follow_ups.molecular_tests.blood_t.description: Numeric value used to describe the lower limit of the normal range used to describe a healthy individual at the institution where the test was completed.

cases.follow_ups.molecular_tests.cell_co.description: Numeric value used to describe the number of cells used for molecular testing.

cases.follow_ups.molecular_tests.chromos.description: A genetic exchange where a piece of one chromosome is transferred to another chromosome.

Under the microscope chromosomes appear as thin, thread-like structures. They all have a short arm and long arm separated by a primary constriction called the centromere. The short arm is designated as p and the long arm as q.

cases.follow_ups.molecular_tests.clonali.description: The text term used to describe whether a genomic variant is related by descent from a single progenitor cell.

cases.follow_ups.molecular_tests.copy_nu.description: Numeric value used to describe the number of times a section of the genome is repeated or copied within an insertion, duplication or deletion variant.

cases.follow_ups.molecular_tests.created.description: A combination of date and time of day in the form [-]CCYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss[Z|(+|-)hh:mm]

cases.follow_ups.molecular_tests.cytoban.description: Alphanumeric value used to describe the cytoband or chromosomal location targeted or included in molecular analysis. If a specific genetic variant is being reported, this property can be used to capture the cytoband where the variant is located. Format: [chromosome][chromosome arm].[band+sub-bands]. Example: 17p13.1.

cases.follow_ups.molecular_tests.days_to.description: Number of days between the date used for index and the date of the laboratory test.
